abstract: Rolando Sarraff Trujillo, intelligence officer freed in prisoner exchange with Cuba, has not contacted his family since being released and his whereabouts are unknown; lengthy debriefing process is common in cases such as his; American officials say he is not being held captive and that he is free to make phone calls.
lead_paragraph: The family of Rolando Sarraff Trujillo has yet to hear from him, and there is suspicion that he is being extensively debriefed before the authorities move him back into society.

byline.contributor: Mark Mazzetti contributed reporting from Washington, and Michael S. Schmidt from Kailua, Hawaii.

headline.main: Whereabouts of U.S. Spy Released in Cuba Deal Are Unknown
